WEBVTT

1
00:02:23.200 --> 00:02:25.040
There you are.

2
00:02:33.960 --> 00:02:36.880
The Sea Snake is going to die.
isn't he?

3
00:02:39.650 --> 00:02:42.430
- Luke...
- I can't be Lord of the Tides.

4
00:02:42.690 --> 00:02:44.970
Grand sire was the greatest sailor
who ever lived.

5
00:02:45.240 --> 00:02:47.830
I get green sick before the ship
even leaves the harbor.

6
00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:50.670
I'll just ruin everything.

7
00:02:51.680 --> 00:02:53.230
I don't want Driftmark.

8
00:02:53.960 --> 00:02:55.240
It should've passed on to Ser Vaemond.

9
00:02:55.440 --> 00:02:58.610
We don't choose our destiny. Luke.
It chooses us.

10
00:02:59.080 --> 00:03:01.790
Grand sire let you choose
whether you'd be his heir.

11
00:03:02.800 --> 00:03:03.920
You told us so.

12
00:03:08.260 --> 00:03:11.000
And do you want to know the truth of it?

13
00:03:13.380 --> 00:03:14.720
I was frightened.

14
00:03:16.330 --> 00:03:19.400
I was four-and-ten.

15
00:03:19.550 --> 00:03:20.890
Same as you are now.

16
00:03:22.090 --> 00:03:25.360
I wasn't ready
to be Queen of the Seven Kingdoms.

17
00:03:26.310 --> 00:03:29.020
But it was my duty.

18
00:03:29.600 --> 00:03:31.940
And. in time. I came to understand

19
00:03:31.940 --> 00:03:33.750
I had to earn my inheritance.

20
00:03:35.500 --> 00:03:36.870
I'm not like you.

21
00:03:37.260 --> 00:03:40.070
- In what way. sweet boy?
- I'm not so...

22
00:03:42.140 --> 00:03:43.140
perfect.

23
00:03:52.590 --> 00:03:55.100
I am anything but.

24
00:03:56.150 --> 00:03:59.470
My father looked after me
and helped to prepare me for my duties.

25
00:04:00.250 --> 00:04:02.600
Your mother will do the same for you.

26
00:04:03.800 --> 00:04:04.880
Good morrow. Princess.

27
00:04:04.890 --> 00:04:06.430
Good morrow. Ser Lorent.

28
00:04:08.180 --> 00:04:10.260
Princess Rhaenys
has just arrived on dragon back.

29
00:04:10.620 --> 00:04:13.360
She urgently requests an audience
with you and Prince Daemon.

30
00:04:31.100 --> 00:04:32.650
The Princess Rhaenys Targaryen.

31
00:04:32.650 --> 00:04:34.150
Thank you. Ser Lorent.

32
00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:40.090
Princess Rhaenys.

33
00:04:40.090 --> 00:04:42.400
might we hope for news
of Lord Corlys's recovery?

34
00:04:42.440 --> 00:04:44.110
Viserys is dead.

35
00:04:50.140 --> 00:04:52.300
I grieve this loss with you. Rhaenyra.

36
00:04:52.460 --> 00:04:55.580
My cousin. your father...

37
00:04:57.200 --> 00:04:58.810
possessed a kind heart.

38
00:05:09.270 --> 00:05:10.430
There is more.

39
00:05:12.170 --> 00:05:15.090
Aegon has been crowned as his successor.

40
00:05:21.750 --> 00:05:23.460
They crowned him?

41
00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:26.770
How did Viserys die?

42
00:05:27.070 --> 00:05:28.430
I could not say.

43
00:05:29.330 --> 00:05:30.970
- How long ago?
- A day past. perhaps two.

44
00:05:30.990 --> 00:05:33.580
I was made a prisoner in my quarters
while the Queen made her preparations.

45
00:05:33.950 --> 00:05:35.110
Viserys has been slain.

46
00:05:37.180 --> 00:05:40.920
Alicent demanded you declare for Aegon.

47
00:05:42.800 --> 00:05:43.920
She did.

48
00:05:46.580 --> 00:05:49.090
- I refused her.
- And yet you are alive.

49
00:05:52.230 --> 00:05:55.310
The High Septon crowned Aegon
in the Dragon pit.

50
00:05:55.340 --> 00:05:58.020
I witnessed it myself
just before I fled on Meleys.

51
00:05:58.430 --> 00:06:01.560
They crowned him before the masses.

52
00:06:01.640 --> 00:06:03.690
So that the masses would see him
as their rightful king.

53
00:06:04.260 --> 00:06:07.310
That whore of a Queen murdered
my brother and stole his throne.

54
00:06:07.360 --> 00:06:09.040
And you could have
burned them all for it.

55
00:06:09.820 --> 00:06:12.740
A war is like to be fought
over this treachery. to be sure.

56
00:06:16.660 --> 00:06:19.020
But that war is not mine to begin.

57
00:06:20.200 --> 00:06:21.590
I only rushed this warning to you

58
00:06:21.590 --> 00:06:23.630
out of loyalty to my husband
and to my house.

59
00:06:26.240 --> 00:06:27.900
The Greens are coming for you. Rhaenyra.

60
00:06:29.350 --> 00:06:30.860
And for your children.

61
00:06:32.480 --> 00:06:34.050
You should leave Dragonstone at once.

62
00:06:53.800 --> 00:06:55.200
The babe is coming.

63
00:07:02.920 --> 00:07:04.510
Her term is far from complete.

64
00:07:04.550 --> 00:07:06.050
This should not be happening.

65
00:07:06.100 --> 00:07:08.240
It is fucking happening.

66
00:07:10.360 --> 00:07:13.080
Keep your head about you. Princess.
Come.

67
00:07:14.340 --> 00:07:16.220
We've done this five times before.

68
00:07:16.220 --> 00:07:18.340
Keep your spirit.
and the sixth will be no different.

69
00:07:18.840 --> 00:07:21.250
Get off. get off. get off. get off!

70
00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:28.590
I want patrols along
the island's perimeter.

71
00:07:28.590 --> 00:07:30.580
looking for any small ships
that might set ashore.

72
00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:34.070
If the Greens attack now.
it will be by stealth...

73
00:07:34.600 --> 00:07:36.000
not directly.

74
00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:37.780
We don't have enough men
to surround the island.

75
00:07:37.780 --> 00:07:39.980
but we can make ourselves
appear stronger than they are.

76
00:07:43.850 --> 00:07:45.840
Conscript the Dragon keepers.
They're capable fighters.

77
00:07:45.840 --> 00:07:48.180
- Waste no time.
- It will be done. my Prince.

78
00:07:59.700 --> 00:08:03.120
- What was that?
- I'm sorry.

79
00:08:04.200 --> 00:08:05.960
You might go easier

80
00:08:05.960 --> 00:08:07.430
on him. my Prince.

81
00:08:08.140 --> 00:08:09.970
so he can learn what
you're trying to teach.

82
00:08:09.980 --> 00:08:11.980
Your lady mother needs to see you!

83
00:08:13.650 --> 00:08:15.400
Both of you.

84
00:08:17.040 --> 00:08:18.500
Mother?

85
00:08:21.360 --> 00:08:22.800
Fuck.

86
00:08:25.010 --> 00:08:26.550
Princess.

87
00:08:37.140 --> 00:08:39.240
Your grand sire. King
Viserys. has passed.

88
00:08:39.340 --> 00:08:40.710
Viserys?

89
00:08:41.040 --> 00:08:43.610
The Greens have
repudiated the succession

90
00:08:43.650 --> 00:08:45.270
and claimed the Iron Throne.

91
00:08:49.350 --> 00:08:51.010
Aegon has been crowned king.

92
00:08:52.100 --> 00:08:54.810
- What is to be done about it?
- Nothing yet.

93
00:08:55.310 --> 00:08:57.670
- And where is Daemon?
- I don't know.

94
00:08:57.730 --> 00:08:59.230
Gone to madness.

95
00:09:00.630 --> 00:09:01.880
Gone to plot his war.

96
00:09:03.570 --> 00:09:06.110
- Leave Daemon with me.
- Jace.

97
00:09:07.200 --> 00:09:08.200
Jacaerys.

98
00:09:13.870 --> 00:09:17.490
Whatever claim remains to me.
you are now its heir.

99
00:09:17.590 --> 00:09:20.590
Naught is to be done but by my command.

100
00:09:34.370 --> 00:09:35.740
A raven flew in this morning.

101
00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:39.030
The Sea Snake's fever has broken.
and he has left Even fall.

102
00:09:39.100 --> 00:09:41.910
- Where is he sailing?
- That much is unclear. my Prince.

103
00:09:42.200 --> 00:09:43.990
We'll send ravens to our nearest allies:

104
00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:46.210
Lords Darklyn. Massey...

105
00:09:47.400 --> 00:09:49.530
- and Bar Emmon.
- Daemon!

106
00:09:50.400 --> 00:09:52.730
Do you want to speak
to the maester. my Prince?

107
00:10:01.450 --> 00:10:03.780
I'll fly to the River lands myself
and affirm Lord Tully's support.

108
00:10:03.780 --> 00:10:05.330
You will do no such thing.

109
00:10:08.120 --> 00:10:11.080
My mother has decreed no action be taken
while she's abed.

110
00:10:17.160 --> 00:10:20.130
It's good you're here. young Prince.

111
00:10:20.480 --> 00:10:22.560
You're needed to patrol
the skies on Vermax.

112
00:10:22.570 --> 00:10:23.900
Did you hear what I said?

113
00:10:27.960 --> 00:10:29.290
The ravens. Lord Bartimos.

114
00:10:31.390 --> 00:10:32.550
I shall see it done.

115
00:10:32.740 --> 00:10:34.040
Summon Ser Steffon.

116
00:10:34.060 --> 00:10:36.200
Our Kings guard are needed
on the Dragonmont.

117
00:10:37.290 --> 00:10:39.900
Come with me. I'll show you
the true meaning of loyalty.

118
00:10:47.540 --> 00:10:49.820
You swore an oath
as knights of the Kings guard.

119
00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:52.440
As do all who wear
the white cloak. my Prince.

120
00:10:53.790 --> 00:10:54.910
To whom?

121
00:10:56.090 --> 00:10:59.120
I swore first to King Jaehaerys.
my Prince.

122
00:11:00.190 --> 00:11:01.400
And then to His Grace.

123
00:11:01.400 --> 00:11:03.510
King Viserys. when he succeeded him.

124
00:11:03.510 --> 00:11:05.490
Do you acknowledge
the true line of succession?

125
00:11:06.170 --> 00:11:07.880
- Yes.
- Yes. my Prince.

126
00:11:14.400 --> 00:11:16.040
Do you recall

127
00:11:16.100 --> 00:11:19.600
who King Viserys named
as his heir before his death?

128
00:11:22.100 --> 00:11:23.640
Princess Rhaenyra.

129
00:11:27.750 --> 00:11:30.070
I'm grateful for
your long service to the crown.

130
00:11:32.200 --> 00:11:34.070
So I'm presenting you with a choice.

131
00:11:56.440 --> 00:11:58.990
Swear anew your oath
to Rhaenyra as your queen...

132
00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:03.810
to Prince Jacaerys as the heir
to the Iron Throne.

133
00:12:08.340 --> 00:12:09.340
Or...

134
00:12:10.180 --> 00:12:12.550
if you support the usurper.
speak it now...

135
00:12:13.640 --> 00:12:15.870
and you will have a clean
and honorable death.

136
00:12:17.090 --> 00:12:19.120
But if you choose treachery.

137
00:12:19.280 --> 00:12:22.380
if you swear fealty now
only to later turn your cloaks...

138
00:12:25.200 --> 00:12:27.470
know that you will die

139
00:12:28.160 --> 00:12:29.160
screaming.

140
00:12:35.160 --> 00:12:37.070
Princess. let us help you.

141
00:12:39.210 --> 00:12:40.720
No.

142
00:12:43.300 --> 00:12:45.950
- Get out!
- Princess. please.

143
00:12:46.230 --> 00:12:47.740
- Get out.
- You should not do this alone. Princess.

144
00:12:47.880 --> 00:12:48.920
Let us help you.

145
00:16:05.470 --> 00:16:07.610
I mean no harm. brothers.

146
00:16:29.160 --> 00:16:30.910
I swear to ward the Queen...

147
00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:35.540
with all my strength...

148
00:16:37.400 --> 00:16:39.460
and give my blood for hers.

149
00:16:44.200 --> 00:16:46.110
I shall take no wife...

150
00:16:47.710 --> 00:16:49.080
hold no lands...

151
00:16:50.580 --> 00:16:52.670
father no children.

152
00:16:53.150 --> 00:16:55.210
I shall guard her secrets

153
00:16:55.500 --> 00:16:57.250
obey her commands

154
00:16:58.780 --> 00:17:01.720
ride at her side. and defend her name
and honor.

155
00:17:27.240 --> 00:17:28.650
My Queen.

156
00:19:07.000 --> 00:19:10.170
Queen Rhaenyra Targaryen.
First of Her Name.

157
00:19:10.200 --> 00:19:13.110
Queen of the Andals and the Rhoynar
and the First Men.

158
00:19:13.300 --> 00:19:16.840
Lady of the Seven Kingdoms
and Protector of the Realm.

159
00:19:21.250 --> 00:19:22.750
Your Grace.

160
00:19:31.500 --> 00:19:33.210
Wine. my Queen.

161
00:19:35.300 --> 00:19:36.630
Thank you. Rhaena.

162
00:19:37.300 --> 00:19:38.380
Come.

163
00:20:02.260 --> 00:20:04.220
- What is our standing?
- We have 30 knights.

164
00:20:04.310 --> 00:20:06.890
a hundred crossbowmen.
and 300 men-at-arms.

165
00:20:06.970 --> 00:20:09.820
Dragons tone is relatively easy to
defend. but as an instrument of conquest.

166
00:20:09.830 --> 00:20:11.980
our army leaves a lot to be desired.

167
00:20:12.010 --> 00:20:14.170
We have sent word to my loyal men
in the City Watch.

168
00:20:14.230 --> 00:20:16.750
I'll have some support there.
but I cannot speak to the numbers.

169
00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:20.500
We already have declarations
from Celtigar and Staunton.

170
00:20:20.520 --> 00:20:23.060
Massey. Darklyn. Bar Emmon.

171
00:20:25.100 --> 00:20:27.180
My lady mother was an Arryn.

172
00:20:27.400 --> 00:20:29.490
The Vale will not turn cloak
against their own kin.

173
00:20:29.490 --> 00:20:32.600
River run was always a close friend
to your father. Your Grace.

174
00:20:32.830 --> 00:20:34.370
With Prince Daemon's acquiescence.

175
00:20:35.000 --> 00:20:37.210
I've already sent ravens to Lord Grover.

176
00:20:40.400 --> 00:20:42.650
Lord Grover is fickle and easily swayed.

177
00:20:42.900 --> 00:20:45.070
He will need to be convinced
of the strength of our position

178
00:20:45.200 --> 00:20:47.990
and that we will support him
should it come to war.

179
00:20:48.100 --> 00:20:50.140
I'm going to treat with him myself.

180
00:20:50.100 --> 00:20:51.610
What of Storm's End and Winter fell?

181
00:20:51.740 --> 00:20:54.020
There has never
lived a Stark who forgot an oath.

182
00:20:54.400 --> 00:20:57.150
And with House Stark.
the North will follow.

183
00:20:57.200 --> 00:21:00.280
Lord Borros Baratheon will need
to be reminded of his father's promises.

184
00:21:13.000 --> 00:21:14.910
What news from Driftmark?

185
00:21:17.520 --> 00:21:19.480
Lord Corlys sails for Dragons tone.

186
00:21:19.700 --> 00:21:21.990
To declare for his Queen.

187
00:21:23.180 --> 00:21:25.840
The Velaryon fleet
is in my husband's yoke.

188
00:21:26.050 --> 00:21:27.720
He decides where they sail.

189
00:21:27.800 --> 00:21:30.590
We shall pray for both you
and your husband's support.

190
00:21:31.200 --> 00:21:34.200
Just as we prayed nightly for the
Sea Snake's return to good health.

191
00:21:35.500 --> 00:21:37.220
There's no port on the Narrow Sea
would dare to make

192
00:21:37.300 --> 00:21:39.170
an enemy of the Velaryon fleet.

193
00:21:40.850 --> 00:21:43.390
- And our enemies?
- We have no friends among the Lannisters.

194
00:21:44.460 --> 00:21:47.460
Tyland has served the Hand
too long to turn against him.

195
00:21:47.700 --> 00:21:49.760
And Otto High tower
needs the Lannister fleet.

196
00:21:49.800 --> 00:21:51.360
Without the Lannisters.
we are not like to find

197
00:21:51.400 --> 00:21:53.650
- any allies west of the Golden Tooth.
- No.

198
00:21:56.360 --> 00:21:58.390
The River lands are essential.
Your Grace.

199
00:21:59.700 --> 00:22:02.840
Pray forgive my bluntness. Your Grace.
but talk of men is moot.

200
00:22:03.600 --> 00:22:07.220
Your cause owns a power
that has not been seen in this world

201
00:22:07.300 --> 00:22:09.500
since the days of Old Valyria.

202
00:22:09.700 --> 00:22:11.030
Dragons.

203
00:22:14.100 --> 00:22:15.510
The Greens have dragons as well.

204
00:22:15.530 --> 00:22:17.330
They have three adults. by my count.
ArshGTX: [Vhagar + Dreamfyre +Sunfyre]

205
00:22:17.400 --> 00:22:19.930
We have Syrax. Caraxes. and Meleys.

206
00:22:20.100 --> 00:22:23.010
Your sons have Vermax.
Arrax. and Tyraxes.

207
00:22:23.100 --> 00:22:24.750
Baela has Moondancer.

208
00:22:24.900 --> 00:22:26.570
Daemon. none of our dragons
have been to war.

209
00:22:26.700 --> 00:22:28.560
There are also unclaimed dragons.

210
00:22:29.000 --> 00:22:31.040
SeaSmoke still resides on Driftmark.
ArshGTX:  Laenor Velaryon`s dragon

211
00:22:31.070 --> 00:22:33.570
Vermithor and SilverWing
dwell on the Dragonmont
ArshGTX:[Dragons of Jaehaerys and his wife]

212
00:22:33.700 --> 00:22:34.780
still riderless.

213
00:22:35.000 --> 00:22:37.050
Then there are the three wild dragons.
all of whom nest here.

214
00:22:38.000 --> 00:22:39.230
And who is to ride them?

215
00:22:39.500 --> 00:22:42.330
Dragonstone has 13 to their 4.

216
00:22:42.400 --> 00:22:45.370
I also have a score of eggs
incubating in the Dragonmont.

217
00:22:46.000 --> 00:22:48.860
Now... we need a place to gather.

218
00:22:48.900 --> 00:22:52.480
a toehold large enough
to house a sizable host.

219
00:22:52.500 --> 00:22:53.730
Here. at Harrenhal.

220
00:22:53.800 --> 00:22:55.970
We cut off the west. surround
King's Landing with the dragons.

221
00:22:55.980 --> 00:22:57.790
And we could have every Green head
mounted on spikes

222
00:22:57.900 --> 00:22:59.710
before the fucking moon turns.

223
00:22:59.900 --> 00:23:01.480
Your Grace...

224
00:23:01.500 --> 00:23:03.190
a ship has been sighted offshore:

225
00:23:03.300 --> 00:23:05.640
a lone galleon. flying a banner
of a three-headed green dragon.

226
00:23:06.200 --> 00:23:08.180
Alert the watchtowers. Sight the skies.

227
00:23:44.000 --> 00:23:46.960
I come at the behest
of the Dowager Queen Alicent.

228
00:23:46.990 --> 00:23:49.150
mother of King Aegon.
Second of His Name.

229
00:23:49.490 --> 00:23:51.740
Lord and Protector of
the Seven Kingdoms.

230
00:23:51.900 --> 00:23:55.900
I've been directed to deliver her
message only to Princess Rhaenyra.

231
00:23:57.800 --> 00:23:59.310
Where is the Princess?

232
00:24:52.000 --> 00:24:53.500
Princess Rhaenyra.

233
00:24:54.080 --> 00:24:55.890
I'm Queen Rhaenyra now.

234
00:24:57.400 --> 00:24:59.560
And you all are traitors to the realm.

235
00:25:00.200 --> 00:25:04.120
King Aegon Targaryen.
Second of His Name...

236
00:25:05.500 --> 00:25:08.660
in his wisdom and desire for peace.

237
00:25:08.700 --> 00:25:10.110
is offering terms.

238
00:25:12.500 --> 00:25:14.110
Acknowledge Aegon as king

239
00:25:14.200 --> 00:25:16.830
and swear obeisance
before the Iron Throne.

240
00:25:16.900 --> 00:25:20.730
In exchange. His Grace will confirm
your possession of Dragon-stone.

241
00:25:21.500 --> 00:25:24.920
It will pass to your true born son.
Jacaerys. upon your death.

242
00:25:25.000 --> 00:25:28.130
Lucerys will be confirmed
as the legitimate heir to Driftmark

243
00:25:28.200 --> 00:25:30.850
and all the lands and holdings
of House Velaryon.

244
00:25:30.900 --> 00:25:32.810
Your sons by Prince Daemon

245
00:25:32.900 --> 00:25:35.810
will also be given places
of high honor at court:

246
00:25:35.860 --> 00:25:38.120
Aegon the Younger as the King's squire.

247
00:25:38.200 --> 00:25:40.110
Viserys as his cupbearer.

248
00:25:40.250 --> 00:25:42.330
Finally. the King. in his good grace.

249
00:25:42.400 --> 00:25:46.520
will pardon any knight or lord
who conspired against his ascent.

250
00:25:47.180 --> 00:25:49.740
I would rather feed
my sons to the dragons

251
00:25:49.800 --> 00:25:52.540
than have them carry shields and cups

252
00:25:53.000 --> 00:25:56.390
for your drunken.
usurper cunt of a king.

253
00:25:56.500 --> 00:25:59.430
Aegon Targaryen sits the Iron Throne.

254
00:26:01.160 --> 00:26:02.850
He wears the Conqueror's crown.

255
00:26:02.930 --> 00:26:04.680
wields the Conqueror's sword.

256
00:26:04.700 --> 00:26:06.110
has the Conqueror's name.

257
00:26:06.200 --> 00:26:08.990
He was anointed by a septon of the Faith

258
00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:10.770
before the eyes of thousands.

259
00:26:10.800 --> 00:26:15.130
Every symbol of
legitimacy belongs to him.

260
00:26:17.050 --> 00:26:20.140
And then there is
Stark. Tully. Baratheon.

261
00:26:20.200 --> 00:26:23.840
Houses that have also received.
and are at present.

262
00:26:23.900 --> 00:26:27.070
considering generous terms
from their king.

263
00:26:29.100 --> 00:26:32.610
Stark. Tully. and Baratheon
all swore to me

264
00:26:32.700 --> 00:26:35.320
when King Viserys named me his heir.

265
00:26:36.100 --> 00:26:40.020
Stale oaths will not put you
on the Iron Throne. Princess.

266
00:26:40.100 --> 00:26:44.020
The succession changed the day
your father sired a son.

267
00:26:44.200 --> 00:26:48.030
I only regret that you and he
were the last to see the truth of it.

268
00:26:49.000 --> 00:26:51.290
You are no more Hand than Aegon is king.

269
00:26:51.410 --> 00:26:52.990
Fucking traitor.

270
00:27:04.600 --> 00:27:06.180
Grand Maester.

271
00:27:11.300 --> 00:27:12.420
What the fuck is this?

272
00:27:27.000 --> 00:27:31.460
Queen Alicent has not forgotten the love
you once had for each other.

273
00:27:32.080 --> 00:27:37.140
No blood need be spilled.
so the realm can carry on in peace.

274
00:27:41.100 --> 00:27:43.290
Queen Alicent eagerly
awaits your answer.

275
00:27:43.400 --> 00:27:45.580
She can have her answer now.
stuffed in her father's mouth

276
00:27:45.600 --> 00:27:46.660
along with his withered cock.

277
00:27:46.700 --> 00:27:48.410
Let's end this mummer's farce.

278
00:27:50.000 --> 00:27:53.210
Ser Erryk. bring me Lord High tower
so I may take the pleasure myself.

279
00:27:57.700 --> 00:27:58.700
No.

280
00:28:10.200 --> 00:28:12.540
King's Landing will have
my answer on the morrow.

281
00:28:34.100 --> 00:28:38.060
It's no easy thing for a man
to be a dragon slayer.

282
00:28:38.100 --> 00:28:41.020
But dragons can kill dragons. And have.

283
00:28:41.100 --> 00:28:44.430
The simple truth is this:
we have more dragons than Aegon.

284
00:28:44.500 --> 00:28:46.830
Viserys spoke often
of the Valyrian histories.

285
00:28:46.900 --> 00:28:48.440
I know them well.

286
00:28:48.900 --> 00:28:51.020
When dragons flew to war...

287
00:28:52.200 --> 00:28:53.570
everything burned.

288
00:28:55.900 --> 00:28:58.780
I do not wish to rule
over a kingdom of ash and bone.

289
00:28:58.800 --> 00:29:01.550
Are you considering the
High towers' terms. Your Grace?

290
00:29:01.800 --> 00:29:05.420
As Queen. what is my true duty
to the realm. Lord Bartimos?

291
00:29:06.100 --> 00:29:07.560
Ensuring peace and unity?

292
00:29:07.580 --> 00:29:10.540
Or that I sit the Iron Throne.
no matter the cost?

293
00:29:10.580 --> 00:29:13.120
- That's your father talking.
- My father's dead.

294
00:29:14.600 --> 00:29:16.720
And he chose me as his successor

295
00:29:19.300 --> 00:29:21.640
to defend the realm.
not cast it headlong into war.

296
00:29:21.700 --> 00:29:23.160
Well. the enemy have declared war.

297
00:29:23.200 --> 00:29:24.780
What are you gonna do about it?

298
00:29:28.400 --> 00:29:29.520
Clear the room.

299
00:29:58.440 --> 00:30:00.060
Does the promise of war excite you?

300
00:30:00.100 --> 00:30:01.990
You cannot bend the knee
to the High towers.

301
00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:03.540
They stole your birthright.

302
00:30:03.600 --> 00:30:05.220
If you could take the Iron Throne

303
00:30:05.300 --> 00:30:07.480
without putting Otto Hightower's
head on a spike.

304
00:30:07.500 --> 00:30:08.960
- would you?
- Are you not angry?

305
00:30:09.100 --> 00:30:11.430
- I should declare war because I'm angry?
- No.

306
00:30:11.450 --> 00:30:13.390
Because it's your duty
as Queen to crush rebellion.

307
00:30:13.400 --> 00:30:17.270
You know my oath
reaches beyond our personal ambitions.

308
00:30:20.300 --> 00:30:22.210
A Song of Ice and Fire.

309
00:30:24.900 --> 00:30:26.020
What?

310
00:30:27.400 --> 00:30:29.120
The coming war against
the darkness in the North.

311
00:30:29.200 --> 00:30:30.740
The Conqueror's Dream.

312
00:30:30.800 --> 00:30:32.880
Viserys shared it with me
when he named me heir.

313
00:30:37.700 --> 00:30:41.630
My brother... was a slave to his
omens and portents.

314
00:30:42.900 --> 00:30:46.200
Anything to make his feckless reign
appear to have purpose.

315
00:30:49.500 --> 00:30:51.510
Dreams didn't make us kings.

316
00:30:52.550 --> 00:30:54.090
Dragons did.

317
00:31:11.300 --> 00:31:12.800
He never told you...

318
00:31:16.800 --> 00:31:17.920
did he?

319
00:31:53.500 --> 00:31:57.230
I've had men whipped for falling asleep
on their watch.

320
00:32:03.400 --> 00:32:04.940
You are no man.

321
00:32:09.350 --> 00:32:11.160
You abandoned me...

322
00:32:13.200 --> 00:32:14.950
when I most needed you.

323
00:32:15.850 --> 00:32:17.810
Both our children stolen from us.

324
00:32:19.400 --> 00:32:20.610
I needed you.

325
00:32:21.200 --> 00:32:22.610
Baela and Rhaena needed you.

326
00:32:22.680 --> 00:32:25.560
and you abandoned us
for more adventure at sea.

327
00:32:25.660 --> 00:32:27.520
As has always been your way.

328
00:32:29.400 --> 00:32:31.540
I had no other place to turn.

329
00:32:33.000 --> 00:32:36.330
- I lost everything.
- We lost. Corlys.

330
00:32:38.050 --> 00:32:39.050
We.

331
00:32:51.350 --> 00:32:53.420
I understand we have a new king.

332
00:32:53.820 --> 00:32:57.150
The Stranger casts a long shadow
over this family.

333
00:33:03.000 --> 00:33:04.550
Your brother is also dead.

334
00:33:09.700 --> 00:33:12.360
In his haste to bury you
and claim your seat.

335
00:33:12.400 --> 00:33:13.900
he stood before the King

336
00:33:13.950 --> 00:33:16.540
and denounced
Laenor's sons as illegitimate.

337
00:33:21.700 --> 00:33:23.940
Daemon took his head for it.

338
00:33:28.100 --> 00:33:32.640
Heedless ambition has always been
a Velaryon weakness.

339
00:33:37.300 --> 00:33:39.110
You were right. Rhaenys.

340
00:33:40.700 --> 00:33:44.040
I reached too far. And for nothing.

341
00:33:46.400 --> 00:33:51.320
Our pursuit of the Iron Throne.
is at an end.

342
00:33:55.480 --> 00:33:58.400
We shall declare for no one.

343
00:33:59.750 --> 00:34:01.610
We will retire to High Tide

344
00:34:01.620 --> 00:34:03.160
to be content...

345
00:34:03.930 --> 00:34:06.300
with our grandchildren

346
00:34:06.340 --> 00:34:09.360
Jace. Luke. and Joff
are claimants to the throne.

347
00:34:10.700 --> 00:34:13.620
Those boys'll not be safe
so long as Aegon is king.

348
00:34:16.100 --> 00:34:20.230
Rhaenyra was complicit
in our son's death.

349
00:34:21.600 --> 00:34:24.020
That girl destroys
everything she touches.

350
00:34:24.030 --> 00:34:25.990
That "girl"...

351
00:34:25.990 --> 00:34:28.290
is holding the realm
together at present.

352
00:34:29.100 --> 00:34:30.690
Every man standing
'round the Painted Table

353
00:34:30.700 --> 00:34:32.820
urges her to plunge the realm into war.

354
00:34:35.300 --> 00:34:38.310
Rhaenyra's the only one
who's demonstrated restraint.

355
00:34:38.350 --> 00:34:41.380
The purpose of war is to fill
graveyards. my dear Lord Staunton.

356
00:34:41.400 --> 00:34:44.480
The trick is to put more of their men
in the ground than your own.

357
00:34:44.800 --> 00:34:46.240
Easy words for a lord who commands

358
00:34:46.300 --> 00:34:47.980
- from the safety of his castle.
- Doesn't make it any less true.

359
00:34:47.990 --> 00:34:49.750
The Lord of the Tides!

360
00:34:50.100 --> 00:34:52.010
Lord Corlys Velaryon.

361
00:34:53.040 --> 00:34:56.280
and his wife.
the Princess Rhaenys Targaryen.

362
00:35:07.200 --> 00:35:08.580
My lords.

363
00:35:08.600 --> 00:35:10.140
Lord Corlys.

364
00:35:11.100 --> 00:35:13.520
It brings much relief to see you hale
and healthy again.

365
00:35:15.850 --> 00:35:18.400
I'm very sorry about your father.
Princess.

366
00:35:19.300 --> 00:35:20.840
He was a good man.

367
00:35:32.100 --> 00:35:33.220
Where is Daemon?

368
00:35:34.200 --> 00:35:37.110
There were other concerns which
demanded the Prince's attention.

369
00:35:48.100 --> 00:35:49.430
Your declared allies?

370
00:35:50.740 --> 00:35:54.160
- Yes.
- Too few to win a war for the throne.

371
00:35:55.750 --> 00:35:58.410
Well. we would also
hope to have the support

372
00:35:58.440 --> 00:36:00.700
- of Houses Arryn. Baratheon. and Stark.

373
00:36:00.750 --> 00:36:02.790
Hope is the fool's ally.

374
00:36:05.600 --> 00:36:08.310
Both Arryn and Baratheon
share blood with my house.

375
00:36:08.350 --> 00:36:10.190
But all of them swore oaths to me.

376
00:36:10.200 --> 00:36:11.930
As did House High tower...

377
00:36:11.940 --> 00:36:13.100
if I remember.

378
00:36:13.400 --> 00:36:15.960
As did you. Lord Corlys.

379
00:36:29.680 --> 00:36:31.010
Your father's realm...

380
00:36:31.900 --> 00:36:34.430
was one of justice and honor.

381
00:36:36.100 --> 00:36:39.880
Our houses are bound by common blood
and common cause.

382
00:36:41.700 --> 00:36:44.320
This High tower treason cannot stand.

383
00:36:49.700 --> 00:36:53.240
You have the full support
of our fleet and house.

384
00:36:54.850 --> 00:36:56.100
Your Grace.

385
00:37:04.400 --> 00:37:06.150
You honor me. Lord Corlys.

386
00:37:12.100 --> 00:37:14.060
Princess Rhaenys.

387
00:37:17.700 --> 00:37:21.170
But. as I said to my bannermen.

388
00:37:21.200 --> 00:37:25.070
I made a promise to my father
to hold the realm strong and united.

389
00:37:26.900 --> 00:37:29.940
If war's first stroke is to fall.
it will not be by my hand.

390
00:37:30.330 --> 00:37:31.700
You do not mean to act?

391
00:37:32.910 --> 00:37:36.110
Taking caution
does not mean standing fast.

392
00:37:36.180 --> 00:37:41.100
I wish to know who my allies are
before I send them to war.

393
00:37:48.400 --> 00:37:50.310
The consequence of my...

394
00:37:50.440 --> 00:37:53.350
near-demise in the Step-stones...

395
00:37:54.480 --> 00:37:56.230
is that we now control them.

396
00:37:57.300 --> 00:37:59.680
I took care to fully garrison
the territory this time.

397
00:37:59.700 --> 00:38:03.970
A total blockade of the shipping lanes
will be in place in days. if not already.

398
00:38:04.660 --> 00:38:06.770
The Triarchy have been routed.

399
00:38:07.280 --> 00:38:09.090
The Narrow Sea is ours.

400
00:38:11.640 --> 00:38:14.230
If we further seal the Gullet.

401
00:38:14.380 --> 00:38:17.180
we can cut off
all seaborne travel and trade

402
00:38:17.280 --> 00:38:18.570
to King's Landing.

403
00:38:19.600 --> 00:38:21.980
I shall take Meleys
and patrol the Gullet myself.

404
00:38:27.080 --> 00:38:29.470
When we drain the Narrow Sea.

405
00:38:29.480 --> 00:38:31.480
we can surround King's Landing

406
00:38:31.500 --> 00:38:33.750
lay siege to the Red Keep

407
00:38:33.800 --> 00:38:36.060
and force the Greens' surrender.

408
00:38:36.100 --> 00:38:39.810
If we are to have enough swords
to surround King's Landing.

409
00:38:39.880 --> 00:38:43.400
we must first secure the support of
Winter fell. the Eyrie. and Storm's End.

410
00:38:43.480 --> 00:38:45.440
I'll prepare the ravens. Your Grace.

411
00:38:46.300 --> 00:38:48.440
We should bear those messages.

412
00:38:49.780 --> 00:38:52.540
Dragons can fly faster than ravens

413
00:38:52.550 --> 00:38:54.090
and they're more convincing.

414
00:38:57.400 --> 00:38:58.520
Send us.

415
00:39:00.600 --> 00:39:02.410
The Prince is right. Your Grace.

416
00:39:11.150 --> 00:39:12.150
Very well.

417
00:39:13.200 --> 00:39:15.540
Prince Jacaerys will fly north.

418
00:39:16.000 --> 00:39:19.160
First to the Eyrie to see my
mother's cousin. the Lady Jeyne Arryn.

419
00:39:19.180 --> 00:39:22.010
and then to Winter fell
to treat with Lord Cregan Stark

420
00:39:22.160 --> 00:39:24.070
for the support of the North.

421
00:39:24.600 --> 00:39:27.190
Prince Lucerys will fly
south to Storm's End

422
00:39:27.240 --> 00:39:30.030
and treat with Lord Borros Baratheon.

423
00:39:30.550 --> 00:39:34.090
We must remind these lords
of the oaths they swore.

424
00:39:35.850 --> 00:39:38.670
And... the cost of breaking them.

425
00:40:01.900 --> 00:40:06.570
It's been said that as Targaryens.
we are closer to Gods than to men.

426
00:40:08.700 --> 00:40:11.610
And the Iron Throne
puts us a touch closer. perhaps.

427
00:40:13.400 --> 00:40:17.320
But. if we are to serve
the Seven Kingdoms...

428
00:40:18.220 --> 00:40:20.130
we must answer to their Gods.

429
00:40:20.900 --> 00:40:25.360
If you take this errand.
you go as messengers. not as warriors.

430
00:40:25.770 --> 00:40:28.210
You must take no part in any fighting.

431
00:40:29.720 --> 00:40:33.890
Swear it to me now
under the eyes of the Seven.

432
00:40:38.330 --> 00:40:39.450
I swear it.

433
00:40:44.110 --> 00:40:45.230
I swear it.

434
00:40:46.090 --> 00:40:47.090
Thank you.

435
00:40:51.110 --> 00:40:53.020
Cregan Stark is...

436
00:40:53.700 --> 00:40:55.780
close to your age than is mine.

437
00:40:55.800 --> 00:41:00.020
I would hope. that as men.
you can find some common interest.

438
00:41:00.280 --> 00:41:01.610
Yes. Your Grace.

439
00:41:09.680 --> 00:41:11.800
Storm's End is a short flight from here.

440
00:41:13.450 --> 00:41:17.120
You have Baratheon blood
from your grandmother. Rhaenys.

441
00:41:17.200 --> 00:41:18.430
And...

442
00:41:18.470 --> 00:41:21.180
Lord Borros is an eternally proud man.

443
00:41:21.750 --> 00:41:25.450
He will be honored
to host a prince of the realm

444
00:41:25.520 --> 00:41:26.850
and his dragon.

445
00:41:35.160 --> 00:41:37.980
I expect you will receive
a very warm welcome.

446
00:41:39.800 --> 00:41:41.550
Yes. Mother. Your Grace.

447
00:41:50.650 --> 00:41:52.310
Go to it then.

448
00:41:58.100 --> 00:42:00.100
ArshGTX: look at the size of Caraxes compared to Vermax
somehow Caraxes age is like grand-grandfather of Vermax

449
00:42:05.720 --> 00:42:07.720
Arrax is a young dragon not suitable for battle

450
00:44:14.110 --> 00:44:16.110
[Vermithor. Jaehaerys dragon]

451
00:45:24.290 --> 00:45:26.210
I am Prince Lucerys Velaryon.

452
00:45:27.040 --> 00:45:29.050
I bring a message to Lord Borros
from the Queen.

453
00:45:45.590 --> 00:45:47.720
Prince Lucerys Velaryon.

454
00:45:53.900 --> 00:45:57.440
Son of Princess Rhaenyra Targaryen.

455
00:46:00.930 --> 00:46:02.260
Lord Borros...

456
00:46:04.000 --> 00:46:06.340
I brought you a message
from my mother...

457
00:46:06.830 --> 00:46:07.950
the Queen.

458
00:46:09.280 --> 00:46:12.460
Yet earlier this day.
I received an envoy from the King.

459
00:46:13.570 --> 00:46:15.140
Which is it?

460
00:46:15.150 --> 00:46:17.860
King or Queen?

461
00:46:18.210 --> 00:46:20.830
The House of the Dragon
does not seem to know who rules it.

462
00:46:23.420 --> 00:46:25.760
What's your mother's message?

463
00:46:40.950 --> 00:46:42.570
Where's the bloody maester?

464
00:47:16.280 --> 00:47:19.150
"Remind" me of my father's oath.

465
00:47:21.170 --> 00:47:23.030
King Aegon at least came with an offer:

466
00:47:23.320 --> 00:47:26.130
my swords and banners
for a marriage pact.

467
00:47:26.900 --> 00:47:29.030
If I do as your mother bids...

468
00:47:30.120 --> 00:47:32.660
which one of my
daughters will you wed?

469
00:47:34.140 --> 00:47:35.520
boy?

470
00:47:36.010 --> 00:47:39.350
My lord... I am not free to marry.

471
00:47:40.400 --> 00:47:41.810
I'm already betrothed.

472
00:47:44.090 --> 00:47:46.310
So you come with empty hands.

473
00:47:48.060 --> 00:47:49.600
Go home. pup.

474
00:47:50.440 --> 00:47:52.610
And tell your mother
that the Lord of Storm's End

475
00:47:52.660 --> 00:47:57.160
is not some dog that she can whistle up
at need to set against her foes.

476
00:47:58.700 --> 00:48:02.530
I shall take your answer
to the Queen. my lord.

477
00:48:08.700 --> 00:48:10.240
Wait...

478
00:48:12.040 --> 00:48:13.580
my Lord Strong.

479
00:48:18.600 --> 00:48:22.330
Did you really think
that you could just fly about the realm

480
00:48:22.400 --> 00:48:24.940
trying to steal my brother's throne
at no cost?

481
00:48:26.500 --> 00:48:28.040
I will not fight you.

482
00:48:29.300 --> 00:48:32.170
I came as a messenger. not a warrior.

483
00:48:32.200 --> 00:48:33.740
A fight would be little challenge.

484
00:48:36.600 --> 00:48:37.720
No.

485
00:48:38.970 --> 00:48:40.880
I want you to put out your eye.

486
00:48:43.120 --> 00:48:44.450
As payment for mine.

487
00:48:46.800 --> 00:48:48.130
One will serve.

488
00:48:52.100 --> 00:48:53.470
I would not blind you.

489
00:48:56.300 --> 00:48:59.340
Plan to make a gift of it to my mother.

490
00:49:02.400 --> 00:49:03.400
No.

491
00:49:04.800 --> 00:49:06.760
Then you are craven
as well as a traitor.

492
00:49:06.800 --> 00:49:08.760
- Not here.
- Give me your eye

493
00:49:09.300 --> 00:49:11.310
or I will take it. bastard!

494
00:49:11.600 --> 00:49:13.510
Not in my hall!

495
00:49:14.300 --> 00:49:15.800
The boy came as an envoy.

496
00:49:15.800 --> 00:49:17.800
I'll not have bloodshed beneath my roof.

497
00:49:18.700 --> 00:49:20.860
Take Prince Lucerys back to his dragon.

498
00:49:21.500 --> 00:49:23.250
Now.

499
00:52:52.710 --> 00:52:56.640
No. no. no. no. no! No. Vhagar! Nooo!

500
00:52:57.800 --> 00:52:59.420
Serve me. Vhagar! No!

501
00:53:21.920 --> 00:53:24.830
Vhagar! No! No.

502
00:55:19.630 --> 00:55:23.130
Another Arya Stark?
